#### Scale Blindness: The Lethal Limitation (Why Bigger Isn't Always Visible)

Humans excel at recognizing threats within our operational scale (1-10 meters, minutes to hours, carbon-based biology). We systematically fail to perceive threats operating on vastly different scales, and we're completely helpless against threats that transcend scale categories entirely. It's like being a 2D character trying to fight a 3D opponent‚Äîexcept the 3D opponent also has time manipulation and reality editing privileges.

