### 2.3 The Mathematics of Defensive Futility

The Multi-Vector Vulnerability Theorem proves that comprehensive defense against multi-paradigm threats is a mathematical impossibility. Every defensive measure creates exploitable vulnerabilities in alternative vectors. It's like trying to plug holes in a dam made of Swiss cheese while the water is made of acid and the plugs are made of sugar.

<div className="bg-gradient-to-br from-red-900/60 to-black/40 border-2 border-red-500/50 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
